
Aim

To identify and define all the actors involved in the Predictive Stock Management System using a CASE tool.

Definition of Actor

An actor is an external entity (user or system) that interacts with the system to achieve specific goals.

Identified Actors
1. Admin

Description:
The Admin is responsible for overall system control and configuration.

Responsibilities:

Manage users and roles

Configure system settings

Monitor system performance

Generate administrative reports

2. Store Manager

Description:
The Store Manager oversees inventory operations and uses predictions for decision-making.

Responsibilities:

View stock predictions

Approve restocking decisions

Monitor inventory levels

Generate inventory reports

3. Inventory Staff

Description:
Inventory Staff handles daily stock operations.

Responsibilities:

Update stock entries

Record incoming and outgoing items

Verify stock levels

4. Supplier

Description:
The Supplier provides stock based on system requests.

Responsibilities:

Receive restock requests

Supply inventory items

Update delivery status

5. Prediction Engine (System Actor)

Description:
An external or automated system component responsible for forecasting stock demand.

Responsibilities:

Analyze historical sales data

Generate stock demand predictions

Send prediction results to the system

6. Sales System (External System)

Description:
An external system that provides sales transaction data.

Responsibilities:

Share sales data

Update transaction records

Actor Summary Table
Actor Name	Actor Type	Role in System
Admin	Human	System administration
Store Manager	Human	Inventory decision-making
Inventory Staff	Human	Stock handling and updates
Supplier	External Entity	Inventory supply
Prediction Engine	System	Demand forecasting
Sales System	External System	Sales data provider
Result

All relevant actors interacting with the Predictive Stock Management System were identified and documented.

Conclusion

Identifying actors helps define system boundaries and user interactions. The Predictive Stock Management System involves human users and external systems to ensure accurate prediction and efficient inventory control.
